Elementary Mathematics or Algebra and Geometry and
English, wit least 50 percent marks (350 out of 700) in aggregate (at least 45 percent marks for Backward Class candidates (3l5 out of 700) in aggregate from recognized schools in Maharashtra State its equivalent.
As per the Notification of the “Department of Higher and Technical Education and Employment” of Govt. of Maharashtra vide No. TEM/1594/63030/TE-1 dated 3/06/1994 the reservation of seats for admission in Rajiv Gandhi Polytechnic Udgir shall be as under Category - Scheduled Caste and SC converted to Buddhism (SC) 13%, Scheduled Tribes (ST) 7%, Denotified Tribes (DT) 3%, Nomadic Tribes (NT-1) 2.5%, Nomadic Tribes (NT-2) 2.5%, Nomadic Tribes (NT-3)	2%, Other Backward Classes (OBC) (including SBC)	19%, There shall be 30% seats reserved for female candidates in the course where the seats for open for male as well as female candidates
The seats reserved for female candidates shall have further reservation among
There shall be 15% seats reserved for the candidates taking Technical Subjects(s) as prescribed by the Board of Technical Examination, Maharashtra State and passing therein in the Secondary School Certificate Examination with qualifying marks as per rule.
For deciding the merit of such candidates, the marks scored by the candidate in the S.S.C Examination without considering the marks scored by him in the Technical Subject(s) shall be considered. Themselves for the categories mentioned above and as per rule

Approval: (AICTE) All India Council of Technical Education
Eligiblity:
For admission to first year of diploma course the candidates must have passed Secondary School Certificate Examination (SSC) or any other equivalent examination with
General Science or Physics & Chemistry
Mathematics or Algebra & Geometry
English
Minimum 35% marks in aggregate are required from recognized schools.
Aggregate marks means :
a) Maharashtra state Board Candidates:
The marks of 5 subjects taken into consideration and mentioned on the mark sheet ( For candidate passed SSC examination after March 2009)
The marks of 5 subjects taken into consideration where hew/she has scored maximum marks ( For candidate passed SSC examination prior March 2009)
Candidate Who have passed Math/Mathematics (Code 71) and Science & Technology (Code 72) are only eligible for admission.
In case of Marks against Sport Activities are given in mark sheet, these shall be added to the aggregate marks for deciding merits.
b) For ICSC Candidates:
Student seeking admission on the basis of Group 1 & Group 2 subjects only, the aggregate marks shall be the grand total of marks in any of the 5 subjects from Group 1 & Group 2 where he/she scored maximum marks.
Students seeking admission on the basis of Group 1, Group 2 & Group 3 Aggregate marks shall be the grand total of all subjects from all groups.
c) For CBSC Candidates:
The aggregate marks means the grand total of marks obtained by the candidate including all subjects as decided on marksheet.
2.For admission to direct second year of diploma course the candidates must have passed
A) Higher Secondary School Certificate Examination ( HSC [10+2] ) or any other equivalent examination with
Vocational / Technical Subject
Mathematics & Geometry
English
Minimum 50% marks in aggregate are required.45% marks are required for backward class Candidates from recognized schools in Maharashtra state only.
OR
B) ITI, ATS or MCVC with minimum 60% marks in following trades

For lateral entry into the second year (III semester) of the three years D.M.E(Tool and Die) course,the candidates shall be required to have passed the higher secondary education(Academic or vocational) of 10,+2 pattern with the following conditions.
i) Academic stream candidate should have compulsorily studied Maths,Physics and Chemistry at 10,+2 level.

Approval: (AICTE) All India Council of Technical Education
Eligiblity:
1. For Admission to First Year Diploma-
Candidate should be an Indian National and should have passed the SSC( Std. X) examination of Maharashtra State Board of Secondary and Higher Secondary or its equivalent with minimum 35 % marks in the best of 5 aggregate (minimum 35 %marks in the Best of 5 aggregate in the case of Backward class categories valid and recognized in the Maharashtra State) with and in subjects Mathematics, General Science and English.
2. For Direct Second Year Admission-
a) HSC with Bi-focal
i) The candidate must have passed H.S.C( Std XII) Technical/ Vocational( Bi-focal) Examination with minimum 50% of marks in aggregate( 45% marks for Backward class).
ii) The candidate must have passed the said examination with and in a technical or vocational subjetcs as prescribed by the Board of Technical Examination, Maharashtra State for different courses.
iii) This admission shall be done by the head of institution, subject to the approval of Jt. Director, Regional Officer of the Directorate of Technical Education, Maharashtra State.
b) For I.T.I Students
The candidate must have passed SSC Exam with following compulsory subjects Mathematics, Science and English and he/she must have passed I.T.I with minimum 60% of marks.
c) HSC
i) The candidate must have passed H.S.C( Std XII) Technical/ Vocational( Bi-focal) Examination with minimum 50% of marks in aggregate( 45% marks for Backward class)
ii) The candidate must have passed the said examination with and in a technical or vocational subjetcs as prescribed by the Board of Technical Examination, Maharashtra State for different courses.
iii) This admission shall be done by the head of institution, subject to the approval of Jt. Director, Regional Officer of the Directorate of Technical Education, Maharashtra State.
Course_Detail: Diploma in Civil Engineering is a three-year full-time course affiliated to Maharashtra State Board of Technical Education, Mumbai and approved by All India Council for Technical Education.

A Pass in HSC (Academic) or (Vocational) courses offered in the Higher Secondary Schools in Tamil Nadu affiliated to the Tamil Nadu Higher Secondary Board with eligibility for University courses of study.

Eligiblity: Candidates for admission into the first semester of full time diploma courses shall be required to have passed 10th Standard or equivalent examinations with Maths and Science as subjects. Note: Lateral entry intake is up to a maximum of 20% sanctioned intake only

College: Shri Laxmanrao Mankar College of Polytechnic, Amgaon

Eligiblity:
First Year Admission in Diploma in Engineering-
Candidates passing SSC examination: Candidate should be an Indian National and should have passed the SSC (Std.X) examination of Maharashtra State Board of Secondary Education or its equivalent examination with subjects with minimum 35% marks. The curriculum will be for 3 years.
Maharashtra State Candidates: Candidate should be an Indian National and should have passed the SSC (Std.X) examination of Maharashtra State Board of Secondary Education or its equivalent examination with subjects with minimum 35% marks. The curriculum will be for 3 years.
Outside Home District Candidates: Candidates will have type of candidature as “Outside Home District” if candidate passing SSC (Std. X) examination from a college outside region. Candidates passing the SSC (Std.X) or its equivalent examination with minimum 50 % marks.
Second Year Admission in Diploma in Engineering-
Candidates passing HSSC examination: Candidate should be an Indian National and should have passed the HSSC (Std.XII) examination of Maharashtra State Board of Secondary and Higher Secondary Education or its equivalent examination with stream science and secured minimum 50% marks aggregate for open category and 45% marks aggregate for backward class category candidates belonging to Maharashtra State only. The curriculum will be for 2 years.
Maharashtra State Candidates: Candidates passing HSSC (Std. XII) examination of Maharashtra State Board of Secondary and Higher secondary Education or its equivalent examination with stream science and secured minimum 50% marks aggregate for open category and 45% marks aggregate for backward class category candidates belonging to Maharashtra State only. The curriculum will be for 2 years.
Outside Home District Candidates: Candidates will have type of candidature as “Outside Home District” if candidate passes either SSC (Std. X) or HSSC (Std. XII) or both the examinations from a college outside region. Candidates passing the HSC (Std. XII) or its equivalent examination with stream science should have secured minimum 50 % marks aggregate for all categories.
Course_Detail: This is a full time three year course affiliated to Maharashtra State Board of Technical Education, Mumbai and approved by AICTE.

Course: Diploma in Electronics and Communication Engineering II Shift
Approval: (AICTE) All India Council of Technical Education
Eligiblity:
1. Must have passed the Karnataka S.S.L.C or equivalent exam by securing 35% marks in Science and Maths. This rule also applies for candidates belonging to Category - I, II(a), II(b), III(a), III(b) and rural category.
2. The candidate should have studied in any of the Karnataka Govt. approved institution from 1st Standard to 10th Standard at least for a period of 5 years. The five years study certificate should be counter signed by the Jurisdictional Block Education Officer.
3. The candidates who have migrated to Karnataka from other states are not eligible to enjoy the reservation Policy of Karnataka Government.
4. Must be in employment as on date in a recognized approved firm/organization with at least three years experience in the field concerned.
5. The candidate should produce along with the application a 'No Objection Certificate' and 'Experience Certificate' issued by the employer concerned and S.S.I Registration Certificate.

Approval: (AICTE) All India Council of Technical Education
Eligiblity:
Candidates for admission in three year diploma shall be required to have passed 10th S.S.L.C Examination (or) The Anglo Indian School Examination with eligibility for Higher Secondary Course in Tamil Nadu (or) any other examination recognized as equivalent to the above by the Board of Secondary Education Tamil Nadu.
Lateral Entry Admission:
For Lateral Entry into the Second year (III Semester) of the three year diploma courses, the candidates shall be required to have passed the Higher Secondary Examination (Academic or Vocational) of 10 plus 2 pattern, with the following conditions:
i. Academic Stream candidates should have compulsorily studied Maths, Physics & Chemistry at 10 + 2 level.
ii. Vocational Stream candidates should have studied either Maths or Physics or Chemistry as one of the subjects of study along with the related Vocational Subject (Theory & Practical) at 10 + 2 level.
iii. HSC / 10 th std with 2 years ITI students can directly join the second year of the three year Diploma programme Their intake is restricted to 20% (10% for Academic + 10% for Vocational) of the sanctioned intake of the I Year Diploma Courses. There is no age limit for the admission.

College: MAEER's MIT College of Railway Engineering and Research, Barshi
Approval: (AICTE) All India Council of Technical Education
Eligiblity: For the candidate of Maharashtra StateIn addition to educational qualification as specified, candidates are required to appear for CET-2018 conducted by concerned Maharashtra State Government Authority.In addition to educational qualification as specified, candidates are required to appear for JEE Main 2018 to be eligible for admission for State Quota (65%) seats through Central Assessment Process (CAP).For candidates outside of Maharashtra State (OMS)In addition to educational qualification as specified, candidates from Maharashtra State as well as outside Maharashtra State are required to appear & qualify in Joint Entrance Examination 2018 (JEE-2018) conducted by C.B.S.E., New Delhi for the Academic Year 2018-19to be eligible for admission.For the candidates wishing admission under Institute Level QuotaCandidates from Maharashtra State as well as from outside Maharashtra State having educational qualification as specified, are eligible for Institute Level Quota seats. However they would have at least appeared for CET / IIT-JEEFor Diploma holder candidatesAfter admissions of candidates fulfilling the eligibility criteria mentioned at para (a, b & c) above, if the vacancies still exist after the cut-off date declared by the concerned Government authority, the Principal may admit diploma holders who have passed the diploma course in Engineering / Technology with minimum of 50% marks (45% Marks for Reserve category and Persons with Disability candidates belonging to Maharashtra State only) and medium of instruction as English from Polytechnics affiliated to MSBTE or AICTE approved autonomous Polytechnics in Maharashtra State. Admissions against Vacant Seats:The applications will be invited for the same from the eligible candidates, after all cap rounds, by the individual colleges to fill these seats. However, eligibility criteria will be as mentioned above. Click here for the requisite list of documents.
